ing stuff at the same time (IE T/L with Rotations + syncing video for instance), and the queuing abilities of SCSI will give you far better throughput.  And you can hook up to as I recall 21 or 22 devices to one controller if it's a three channel controller.....<br>
<br>
And if you're going to go with more then 4 disk devices (CD/DVD/Disk) you probably want to consider 400-450W power supplies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugorgarthegreat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gorgar the Great</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~thorvard/Pics/flake.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 12:13:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~thorvard/Pics/Gorgar.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hardware geeks wanted... advice needed.</span><hr size=1> I suggest you build a seperate gaming rig and work rig. You'll be much better off that way. You'll use less resources and generate way less heat. The rig you have in mind sounds like a nightmare to configure. <p><img src="http://squirming.net/meme/tests/affliction/rabies.gif" title="I am Rabies. Grrrrrrrr!"><br \><a href="http://squirming.net/meme/tests/affliction/">Take the Affliction Test Today!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unexc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nexc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/4/02 2:29:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=207.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hardware geeks wanted... advice needed.</span><hr size=1> To support the 2 extra HDs needed you could go with a promise fasttrak controller and stripe the additional 2 drives.  I use one in my system and it helps throughput quite a bit.<br>
